    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment outcome is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) — is accepted under a risk-informed rationale: the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 standard configuration, and the clinical loading envelope is conservatively covered by the standard worst-case geometry. Quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs across N=11 constructs and two independent laboratories. Package conforms to ProfileMinimal; signature workflow is pending organisational PKI provisioning and has not yet been applied.",
